'''Bahaa al-Farra''' ({{lang-ar|بهاء الفرا}}; born 10 March 1991) is a [[State of Palestine|Palestinian]] runner from Gaza. He competed at the [[2012 Summer Olympics]] in the [[Athletics at the 2012 Summer Olympics – Men's 400 metres|400 m]] event, posting a season's best time of 49.93 seconds despite being eliminated in the first round. Along with [[Woroud Sawalha]] he was one of two runners representing Palestine.<ref>[http://www.london2012.com/athlete/al-farra-bahaa-1091438/ Profile]</ref>

