The '''Slovenian Alpine Museum''' ({{lang-sl|Slovenski planinski muzej}}), also the '''Slovenian Mountaineering Museum''', is a [[mountaineering]] museum in [[Mojstrana]], in the vicinity of [[Triglav National Park]] ([[Julian Alps]]), in northwestern [[Slovenia]]. It was opened on 7 August 2010 by [[Danilo Türk]], the then [[President of Slovenia]]. It is operated by the [[Jesenice Upper Sava Museum]]. In June 2016, the Swiss King Albert I Memorial Foundation bestowed it the {{ill|Albert Mountain Award|de}} for its important contribution to the sustainable development of the [[Alps|Alpine]] space.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.rtvslo.si/news-in-english/royal-recognition-for-slovenian-alpine-museum/396083 |title=Royal Recognition for Slovenian Alpine Museum |publisher=MMC RTV Slovenija |date=19 June 2016}}</ref>

