'''''The Cyclist''''' ({{lang-fa|بايسيكلران}} ''Bicycleran'') is a 1987 [[Iran]]ian sports-drama film written and directed by [[Mohsen Makhmalbaf]], starring Moharram Zaynalzadeh as Nasim.

==Plot==
Nasim, a poor [[Afghan refugees|Afghan refugee]] in Iran, gives a demonstration in his town's square where he rides his bicycle without stopping for seven days and seven nights, with the aim of raising money for life-saving surgery for his dying wife. In the end, even after seven days, he continues to pedal endlessly, too fatigued to hear his son's and the crowd's pleas to get off his bicycle.<ref>{{harvnb|Adelkhah|Olszewska|2007|p=137}}</ref> One scholar analyses the film as an [[allegory]] which parallels the exploitation that Afghan refugees suffer from in Iran and from which they are unable to escape.<ref>{{harvnb|Adelkhah|Olszewska|2007|p=138}}</ref>

==Accolades==
In 1991 the film won the best feature film award in the [[Hawaii International Film Festival]].{{Citation needed|date=June 2011}}

